n typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:ea typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="-122"/><a:cs typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="-120"/></a:rPr><a:t>The citizen science model is not tied to a single geography or topic. The key is not to copy an exact project, but to replicate the </a:t></a:r><a:pPr algn="l" indent="0" marL="0"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPct val="127000"/></a:lnSpc><a:buNone/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="850" b="1" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="443728"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Open Sans Bold" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:ea typeface="Open Sans Bold" pitchFamily="34" charset="-122"/><a:cs typeface="Open Sans Bold" pitchFamily="34" charset="-120"/></a:rPr><a:t>method</a:t></a:r><a:pPr algn="l" indent="0" marL="0"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPct val="127000"/></a:lnSpc><a:buNone/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="850" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="443728"/></a:solidFill><a:latin typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="0"/><a:ea typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="-122"/><a:cs typeface="Open Sans" pitchFamily="34" charset="-120"/></a:rPr><a:t>: clear scientific goals, accessible participation, rigorous protocols, feedback loops, and strong local partnerships. A coastal area may focus on marine biodiversity; an urban area on air quality, heat islands, or mosquitoes.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr lang="en-US" sz="850" dirty="0"/></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:pic>  <p:nvPicPr><p:cNvPr id="4" name="Image 0" descr="preencoded.png">    </p:cNvPr>    <p:cNvPicPr><a:picLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></p:cNvPicPr>    <p:nvPr></p:nvPr>  </p:nvPicPr><p:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId1"></a:blip>  <a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></p:blipFill><p:spPr> <a:xfrm>  <a:off x="626641" y="1540222"/>  <a:ext cx="7890644" cy="2960936"/> </a:xfrm> <a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom></p:spPr></p:pic><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="5" name="Text 2"></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr/><p:nvPr></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:x